1) increased membrane peroxidation in the SNc and widespread ROS-induced protein modification, with protein carbonyl levels elevated in all regions of the brain [7,8];;
2) elevated TBA-reactive substance levels (a measure of the secondary products of lipid peroxidation) accompanied by decreased PUFA levels (the peroxidation substrate) [8];;
