There are several potential metabolic sources of increased oxidative stress in PD: dopamine metabolism, mitochondrial dysfunction, increased free iron levels, accumulation of AGEs, reduced activity of free radical defense systems, and the deleterious role of glial cells. Several toxins may also be implicated in PD. A brief discussion is devoted to each of these hypotheses.
